Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro and Grupo Financiero Galicia

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-04-14T21:37:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-and-grupo-financiero-galicia.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 0.8 percent to 3,381.57.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   retreated 3.4 percent to 16.80
pesos. The Argentine lender fell as the price of local
 government bonds  declined, signaling a lower value for banks’
fixed income holdings.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  ,  Argentina ’s largest
consumer lender, fell 1.6 percent to 5.63 pesos. “Argentina’s
market is moving in line with lower global equity markets,”
Alberto Tarsia, a trader at Debursa Sociedad de Bolsa SA, said
today in a telephone interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
